00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Downloaded From www.AllSubs.org

1
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:54,077
<i>What a humiliation.</i>

2
00:01:56,727 --> 00:01:59,719
<i>A lot of unhappiness
around the Bernabéu tonight,</i>

3
00:01:59,807 --> 00:02:03,482
<i>a lot of it directed at Gavin Harris.
Came out as a hero,</i>

4
00:02:03,567 --> 00:02:05,478
<i>he's being called a donkey tonight.</i>

5
00:02:19,327 --> 00:02:22,842
<i>Ronaldinho seals it
with a brilliant third.</i>

6
00:02:28,927 --> 00:02:32,237
<i>Boy, do they need
some inspiration from somewhere.</i>

7
00:02:37,127 --> 00:02:41,120
<i>And now it's Munez. And we
haven't seen too much of him today.</i>

8
00:02:41,207 --> 00:02:44,563
<i>Trying a give-and-go here
with Alan Shearer.</i>

9
00:02:44,647 --> 00:02:47,320
<i>What a great run by Munez!</i>

10
00:02:48,727 --> 00:02:53,437
<i>Unbelievable!
Newcastle's newest and youngest player</i>

11
00:02:53,527 --> 00:02:56,485
<i>gives the fans a brand-new song to sing.</i>

12
00:03:00,287 --> 00:03:03,677
<i>He's got support to his right.</i>

13
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:06,758
<i>Stephen Carr.</i>

14
00:03:07,527 --> 00:03:09,483
<i>A great header!</i>

15
00:03:10,887 --> 00:03:12,718
<i>And a goal!</i>

16
00:03:12,807 --> 00:03:15,321
<i>It's a dream start for Newcastle!</i>

17
00:03:56,447 --> 00:03:59,245
- OK.
- What about the rose petals?

18
00:03:59,327 --> 00:04:02,842
About bloody time. Can we have
the red rose petals, but in that?

19
00:04:12,127 --> 00:04:14,118
- Gotta get back to work.
- Hey, babe.

20
00:04:14,207 --> 00:04:16,596
- OK. Hello.
- Hey.

21
00:04:16,687 --> 00:04:18,678
Just no fuss.

22
00:04:18,767 --> 00:04:20,997
I've got to go,
but I will see you Tuesday.

23
00:04:21,087 --> 00:04:23,555
- All right. Bye.
- Bye-bye.

24
00:04:24,527 --> 00:04:28,315
San, it's ten of 5.00. The meeting
with the wedding planner was at 4.00.

25
00:04:28,407 --> 00:04:31,160
Sorry, babe. I just...
I lost track of time.

26
00:04:31,247 --> 00:04:34,284
- We do this together.
- What do I know about flowers?

27
00:04:34,367 --> 00:04:36,961
As long as you show up,
I'll be happy.

28
00:04:37,047 --> 00:04:39,561
You Latin boys are so cheeky.
Do you know that?

29
00:04:39,647 --> 00:04:42,480
- Are you gonna show up?
- I might, if you're lucky.

30
00:04:43,447 --> 00:04:45,722
Oh, no. Go and have a shower. You stink.

31
00:04:59,807 --> 00:05:01,445
It's time for a toast, I think.

32
00:05:01,527 --> 00:05:04,724
To your new home, may all your ups
and downs be in the bedroom.

33
00:05:04,807 --> 00:05:06,638
Mom!

34
00:05:08,167 --> 00:05:11,443
You might want to be careful, Santi.
Look where it got me!

35
00:05:11,527 --> 00:05:13,438
You're lucky I let you get near me.

36
00:05:13,527 --> 00:05:17,076
- How about the extra hot vindaloo?
- Sounds good.

37
00:05:17,167 --> 00:05:20,204
Have consideration.
I'm the one who has to sleep with him.

38
00:05:20,287 --> 00:05:23,597
It sounds good.

39
00:05:23,687 --> 00:05:25,484
- Hello, stranger.
- Hello.

40
00:05:25,567 --> 00:05:28,684
What happened?
Did you lose me number?

41
00:05:28,767 --> 00:05:31,327
- Good timing. We're ordering.
- Can I have a word?

42
00:05:31,407 --> 00:05:34,240
- Yeah, sure.
- In private?

43
00:05:34,327 --> 00:05:35,760
Excuse us.

44
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:49,325
Oh, my God.

45
00:05:50,487 --> 00:05:52,682
I've been on the phone for hours.

46
00:05:53,967 --> 00:05:55,719
Are they serious?

47
00:05:58,007 --> 00:05:59,520
They want to meet us.

48
00:06:14,047 --> 00:06:16,197
- Shtoom, though, OK?
- Yeah.

49
00:06:16,687 --> 00:06:18,917
You've got two more years
with Newcastle.

50
00:06:19,007 --> 00:06:21,760
The fans'll go mad.
You're the best player.

51
00:06:21,847 --> 00:06:23,963
It's just a meeting.

52
00:06:24,047 --> 00:06:27,562
So when are they coming to meet us?

53
00:06:27,647 --> 00:06:31,322
They're not.
I'm meeting them in Japan.

54
00:07:08,127 --> 00:07:11,119
The biggest football club on the planet.

55
00:07:11,207 --> 00:07:15,837
Nine times European champions.
Twenty-nine Spanish League titles.

56
00:07:15,927 --> 00:07:19,476
Twelve Spanish Cups.
One Super Cup.

57
00:07:20,207 --> 00:07:23,244
They come to Tokyo every summer,
the whole squad.

58
00:07:23,327 --> 00:07:27,843
Beckham, Raúl,
Ronaldo, Roberto Carlos,

59
00:07:27,927 --> 00:07:32,159
Zidane, Harris, Munez.

60
00:08:01,087 --> 00:08:03,840
Won't be long, don't worry.

61
00:08:07,127 --> 00:08:08,958
Thank you for coming.

62
00:08:09,047 --> 00:08:10,878
- Santi, how are you?
- Fine thank you.

63
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:12,195
Welcome to this
legendary football club.

64
00:08:13,327 --> 00:08:15,204
I wanted to introduce you
to our coach.

65
00:08:15,287 --> 00:08:17,323
- Van der Merwe.
- Pleased to meet you.

66
00:08:18,287 --> 00:08:21,404
- Sorry you had to come so fast.
- That's fine.

67
00:08:21,487 --> 00:08:24,365
We want Santiago.
We can make this work.

68
00:08:24,447 --> 00:08:28,326
We have to act quickly. The transfer
window closes tomorrow at midnight.

69
00:08:28,407 --> 00:08:31,444
- I know. Let's vamoose.
- OK. Come on.

70
00:08:34,887 --> 00:08:37,082
Just don't think about the money.

71
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:41,080
You're gonna hate Madrid.
They all speak bloody Spanish.

72
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:42,646
- How's it going?
- Good.

73
00:08:42,727 --> 00:08:45,082
- We haven't said yes yet.
- What, are you mad?

74
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:50,161
With ten percent you have your chest
waxed and highlights. You're sorted.

75
00:08:50,247 --> 00:08:52,886
It's a big decision.
Roz and I got this new house.

76
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:55,435
You came halfway around
the world for karaoke?

77
00:08:55,527 --> 00:08:58,485
No one says no to Real Madrid,
you nutter.

78
00:08:58,567 --> 00:09:02,765
I don't wanna be on the bench like Owen.
He's one of the best. I'd go crazy.

79
00:09:04,487 --> 00:09:06,000
- It's Dutch.
- Gentlemen.

80
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:08,282
<i>Herr Van der Merwe.
Can I get you a drink?</i>

81
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:11,723
Thank you. You're not
giving any career advice, are you?

82
00:09:11,807 --> 00:09:14,241
He's pretending
he's got a decision to make.

83
00:09:14,327 --> 00:09:16,158
I have some advice.

84
00:09:16,247 --> 00:09:18,078
First, you listen to your heart.

85
00:09:18,167 --> 00:09:21,239
Then you listen to your head.

86
00:09:21,327 --> 00:09:23,443
Then your wife will
tell you what to do.

87
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:35,358
You're OK, Mr Ives.

88
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:42,478
Sorry, doctor.

89
00:09:52,207 --> 00:09:53,242
No comment!

90
00:09:55,087 --> 00:09:57,647
Don't leave, Santi! Don't leave!

91
00:09:58,607 --> 00:10:01,804
<i>[woman on TV] Michael Owen
acknowledges the Newcastle fans</i>

92
00:10:01,887 --> 00:10:03,923
<i>as they welcome him
to St James's Park.</i>

93
00:10:04,007 --> 00:10:06,567
<i>The last-minute exchange deal
with Real Madrid</i>

94
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:10,959
<i>will see Santiago Munez move
to Real Madrid on a two-year contract.</i>

95
00:10:15,367 --> 00:10:18,359
- Excuse me. You know where Roz is?
- Down to the left.

96
00:10:18,447 --> 00:10:19,800
Thank you.

97
00:10:20,807 --> 00:10:25,119
There's that git,
upsetting my lovely Rosalind.

98
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:27,402
You're in the bad books now.

99
00:10:27,487 --> 00:10:29,955
- Hey, you save your breath, Mr Ives.
- Baby.

100
00:10:30,047 --> 00:10:32,481
- I don't want to talk to you.
- I tried to call.

101
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:35,957
- You should've asked for more time.
- I tried. Hey, listen.

102
00:10:36,047 --> 00:10:40,006
I love you. I love you and I want
to marry you. None of that changes.

103
00:10:40,087 --> 00:10:43,124
Now, before we have kids
and responsibilities, we can...

104
00:10:43,207 --> 00:10:45,801
- Stop playing with the bed.
- I'm sorry.

105
00:10:45,887 --> 00:10:49,846
We can go places, do things.
Just you and me.

106
00:10:53,207 --> 00:10:56,643
I'm not sure I want to live in Spain.
I mean...

107
00:10:57,167 --> 00:11:00,125
- I love Newcastle.
- I love it too. It's been good to me.

108
00:11:00,207 --> 00:11:04,086
If I hadn't come I wouldn't have found
the most important thing in my life:

109
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:07,557
- You.
- He's got a point there.

110
00:11:07,647 --> 00:11:12,357
Yeah, and what about our wedding and
our new house and my job? I love my job.

111
00:11:12,447 --> 00:11:14,836
- I know, but...
- I've got exams at Easter.

112
00:11:14,927 --> 00:11:18,681
You can see me on your days off,
how's that? I'll fly back when I can.

113
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:22,646
Baby, I can't walk away
from this chance.

114
00:11:22,727 --> 00:11:28,040
This is my life,
and I want you there... with me.

115
00:11:29,207 --> 00:11:32,279
- I can't even speak Spanish.
- I'll teach you.

116
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:37,886
I'm not eating paella.

117
00:11:40,247 --> 00:11:43,125
Hey, hey, hey. Come here.

118
00:11:44,687 --> 00:11:49,124
Will you do us a favour?
When you see that Gavin Harris,

119
00:11:49,207 --> 00:11:51,675
tell him he's shite.

120
00:12:07,127 --> 00:12:11,120
- I love you.
- I love you.

121
00:13:05,487 --> 00:13:07,318
A very good day to all of you

122
00:13:07,807 --> 00:13:10,605
and thank you for coming

123
00:13:11,047 --> 00:13:15,086
to this very important presentation

124
00:13:15,407 --> 00:13:18,046
of one of the greatest players
in the world

125
00:13:18,567 --> 00:13:20,046
Good luck in this team.

126
00:13:20,447 --> 00:13:22,324
Best wishes
and we place our hopes in you.

127
00:13:22,407 --> 00:13:23,886
Many thanks.

128
00:13:32,967 --> 00:13:37,916
<i>Over ten thousand fans turned up
to welcome Real's latest signing...</i>

129
00:13:40,407 --> 00:13:44,605
<i>Newcastle United fans are still coming
to terms with the loss of Santiago,</i>

130
00:13:44,687 --> 00:13:47,918
<i>two years before the end
of his contract...</i>

131
00:13:53,007 --> 00:13:57,046
<i>...in exchange for Michael Owen
has shocked fans...</i>

132
00:13:57,127 --> 00:14:01,757
<i>...the Mexican-born striker runs
the risk of sitting on the bench.</i>

133
00:14:02,687 --> 00:14:04,405
How much do you think this one cost?

134
00:14:04,847 --> 00:14:06,326
I couldn't care less
if the Bernabéu goes bankrupt.

135
00:14:06,407 --> 00:14:09,444
<i>We have the best strikers.
We all know that.</i>

136
00:14:09,527 --> 00:14:11,961
<i>They compete with each other.</i>

137
00:14:12,047 --> 00:14:15,119
<i>No player wants
to be on the bench for a long time.</i>

138
00:14:15,207 --> 00:14:18,279
<i>I'm sure it's not that
different for Mr Munez.</i>

139
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:23,316
<i>Well, I've always been a fan of Real
Madrid. Me, my grandma, my brother.</i>

140
00:14:23,407 --> 00:14:26,877
<i>It's like a dream come true for me
to be playing on this team, yeah.</i>

141
00:14:27,607 --> 00:14:28,960
Goal!

142
00:14:29,047 --> 00:14:31,515
<i>Is it true only a year ago
you were a gardener?</i>

143
00:14:31,607 --> 00:14:36,442
<i>I'm from a simple background. My story's
different than most of the players.</i>

144
00:14:36,527 --> 00:14:39,644
<i>- Rosa. Rosa!
- For me, it's a big thing.</i>

145
00:14:39,727 --> 00:14:41,126
<i>A big responsibility.</i>

146
00:14:41,207 --> 00:14:43,880
The omelette. It's lunchtime.

147
00:14:43,967 --> 00:14:46,003
<i>I'll try to be at the same level.</i>

148
00:14:46,087 --> 00:14:50,000
<i>It's an honour to play with great
players like Zidane and David,</i>

149
00:14:50,087 --> 00:14:52,681
<i>Roberto Carlos, everybody, so...</i>

150
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:55,600
<i>You're prepared
for everything about to hit you?</i>

151
00:15:19,407 --> 00:15:23,241
- First day of school. Make me proud.
- I will, Mama.

152
00:16:52,807 --> 00:16:55,002
- Miss Harmison?
- Hey.

153
00:16:58,447 --> 00:17:01,644
Where have you been?
Training or shopping? Oh, my God.

154
00:17:01,727 --> 00:17:05,436
- It's for us, baby. It's for us.
- Have they given you all this?

155
00:17:07,087 --> 00:17:10,045
- Wow. Can I have one?
- Sure. They're for you.

156
00:17:12,407 --> 00:17:14,841
Pick a car. Any car.

157
00:17:14,927 --> 00:17:18,237
- You'll have to score a lot of goals.
- I'll try.

158
00:17:19,687 --> 00:17:23,919
<i>The UEFA Champions League is back,
and it's back at the Santiago Bernabéu.</i>

159
00:17:24,007 --> 00:17:27,397
<i>What a stage
for Europe's top club competition.</i>

160
00:17:30,767 --> 00:17:33,122
- Hey.
- Look at this.

161
00:17:33,207 --> 00:17:35,163
Oh, my God.

162
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:38,724
Look at that.

163
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:43,119
<i>Real Madrid, nine times winners.
But not now for four years.</i>

164
00:17:43,207 --> 00:17:46,438
<i>This is where they kick off
their latest campaign.</i>

165
00:17:46,527 --> 00:17:50,361
<i>An unhappy time for Gavin Harris.
He has a point to prove.</i>

166
00:17:51,287 --> 00:17:53,323
- Cheers. Good luck.
- Cheers.

167
00:18:01,327 --> 00:18:05,286
<i>The new boy, Munez.
He starts from the bench.</i>

168
00:18:26,287 --> 00:18:30,485
<i>Gavin Harris. He hasn't scored
for 14 games. The wait goes on.</i>

169
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:32,285
<i>Half a yard behind, isn't he?</i>

170
00:18:53,327 --> 00:18:55,636
<i>Just over half an hour to go.</i>

171
00:18:56,927 --> 00:18:58,963
<i>Again the delivery. No finish.</i>

172
00:19:02,687 --> 00:19:07,238
<i>Harris again trying to influence
proceedings. He's struggling tonight.</i>

173
00:19:14,607 --> 00:19:16,962
<i>One on one,
that should have been a goal.</i>

174
00:19:25,047 --> 00:19:27,766
<i>Harris off the mark, off his game.</i>

175
00:19:30,247 --> 00:19:33,398
<i>And the crowd's starting
to get on the Englishman's back.</i>

176
00:19:34,367 --> 00:19:37,404
<i>- Oh, yeah, look, there he is.
- It's time for a new star.</i>

177
00:19:37,487 --> 00:19:40,240
<i>Does this spell the end
for Gavin Harris?</i>

178
00:19:44,527 --> 00:19:48,486
<i>It's certainly the start
of something new for Santiago Munez.</i>

179
00:19:49,247 --> 00:19:51,158
- Go, Sant.
- Go on, Santi.

180
00:19:59,847 --> 00:20:03,556
<i>Munez ghosting in.
He's looking menacing.</i>

181
00:20:07,847 --> 00:20:12,045
<i>Oh, dear, it's all coming to the boil.
Thomas Gravesen's brought his handbag.</i>

182
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:15,042
<i>Beckham's corner.</i>

183
00:20:15,127 --> 00:20:17,800
<i>Not cleared,
only as far as Munez.</i>

184
00:20:17,887 --> 00:20:19,957
<i>Could this be the moment?!</i>

185
00:20:22,967 --> 00:20:24,923
Yes! Yes!

186
00:20:34,127 --> 00:20:38,279
<i>It could not be a better start
to his Real Madrid career.</i>

187
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:40,562
<i>A last-minute goal for Santiago Munez.</i>

188
00:20:52,807 --> 00:20:53,842
- Enrique!
- Come on, come on.

189
00:20:54,207 --> 00:20:55,799
- Did you bring the dough?
- Quick, before they catch us.

190
00:20:56,007 --> 00:20:57,440
OK, OK, this is for you
and this is for me.

191
00:20:59,327 --> 00:21:00,646
What's in that head of yours?

192
00:21:00,727 --> 00:21:03,525
What do you want?
For us to visit you in jail?

193
00:21:03,767 --> 00:21:04,756
Listen...

194
00:21:05,487 --> 00:21:09,639
...one false move,
and you will ruin your life forever.

195
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:11,319
More ruined than it already is?

196
00:21:12,647 --> 00:21:15,400
Enrique my love, don't say that.

197
00:21:16,687 --> 00:21:18,405
Look at that player, Munez.

198
00:21:19,127 --> 00:21:21,436
He didn't have anything, like you.

199
00:21:21,727 --> 00:21:23,046
Look at him now.

200
00:21:23,287 --> 00:21:26,882
Apart from that, what the hell
does that have to do with me?

201
00:21:29,727 --> 00:21:34,084
I'm going to tell you a secret.
That player is your brother.

202
00:21:36,647 --> 00:21:38,797
Santi! Over here!

203
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:42,400
- OK, OK. Take it easy.
- Santi!

204
00:21:43,047 --> 00:21:46,517
- Come on out, darling.
- Careful. Are you all right?

205
00:21:46,607 --> 00:21:49,121
- Are you OK?
- I broke my heel off.

206
00:21:50,727 --> 00:21:54,640
Come on inside. I've got a little
surprise for you. This way.

207
00:21:56,727 --> 00:21:57,716
That's for you.

208
00:21:58,407 --> 00:22:01,205
Come on in. And follow me. Follow me.

209
00:22:04,727 --> 00:22:06,160
That's for you.

210
00:22:07,527 --> 00:22:09,518
- Come on. This way.
- What was that?

211
00:22:09,607 --> 00:22:11,643
Come on. Patience.

212
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:16,642
And pick her up. She can't walk.

213
00:22:30,447 --> 00:22:31,880
And that's for you.

214
00:22:35,007 --> 00:22:37,965
Come here.
I think he wants a photo.

215
00:22:38,047 --> 00:22:39,799
Here we go.

216
00:22:41,927 --> 00:22:46,478
- So is it always like this or what?
- It is, actually. They're all mad.

217
00:22:47,487 --> 00:22:50,285
- Total lunatics.
- You don't sound surprised.

218
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:53,439
- You love it.
- What, being in the press?

219
00:22:53,527 --> 00:22:56,599
I'll tell you what.
At the end of the day,

220
00:22:56,687 --> 00:23:00,726
I'd rather be out with my friends having
a nice meal, nice conversation.

221
00:23:01,847 --> 00:23:03,599
Let it breathe for one minute.

222
00:23:03,687 --> 00:23:07,362
OK. There's more
to life than just football.

223
00:23:07,447 --> 00:23:09,836
What, like computer games?

224
00:23:09,927 --> 00:23:13,476
- Come on, you're in the first team.
- Don't get me wrong.

225
00:23:13,567 --> 00:23:17,355
It pays the bills. I do love it,
but I've got other interests as well.

