Well, did he say anything else?

457
00:45:56,047 --> 00:45:58,436
No, nothing.
When he threw that at me,

458
00:45:58,527 --> 00:46:01,644
I was so freaked I just drove off.
I couldn't breathe.

459
00:46:01,727 --> 00:46:06,482
It might not be bad. You always
talked about wanting to find her.

460
00:46:06,567 --> 00:46:10,765
I know. But right now, I can't deal with
it. In my head, she was gone forever.

461
00:46:13,047 --> 00:46:15,322
She does really look like you.

462
00:46:30,607 --> 00:46:32,802
<i>- Hey.
- Santiago.</i>

463
00:46:32,887 --> 00:46:35,526
<i>- Where did you get this?
- Is it her, Grandma?</i>

464
00:46:36,767 --> 00:46:41,045
When you went to Spain,
I worried this might happen.

465
00:46:41,127 --> 00:46:42,924
Wait, you knew?

466
00:46:43,007 --> 00:46:47,285
I couldn't tell you, Santiago.
I didn't want to cause you pain.

467
00:46:47,367 --> 00:46:49,642
<i>My God. You didn't tell me?</i>

468
00:46:49,727 --> 00:46:52,958
<i>- What gave you the right?
- That woman left all of us.</i>

469
00:46:53,047 --> 00:46:56,835
She just walked away.
Left your father in pieces.

470
00:46:56,927 --> 00:46:58,883
But it's my choice.
She's my mother.

471
00:46:58,967 --> 00:47:02,164
<i>She abandoned you.
How can you forgive her for that?</i>

472
00:47:02,247 --> 00:47:04,636
OK, Grandma. Let me decide, please.

473
00:47:33,447 --> 00:47:35,517
Santi! Santi! Santi!

474
00:48:14,367 --> 00:48:16,278
Santi, you listening?

475
00:48:33,287 --> 00:48:35,437
<i>It's a very big night
for that young man.</i>

476
00:48:35,527 --> 00:48:39,281
<i>Santiago Munez, for the first time
since his move from Newcastle,</i>

477
00:48:39,367 --> 00:48:42,279
<i>starts a game for Real Madrid.</i>

478
00:48:42,367 --> 00:48:45,518
<i>Illustrious company alongside him,
to say the least.</i>

479
00:48:45,607 --> 00:48:48,075
<i>Just look at those names.</i>

480
00:48:51,847 --> 00:48:56,557
<i>They tend to be feisty, these encounters
between Real Madrid and Valencia.</i>

481
00:48:58,447 --> 00:49:00,677
<i>It's Beckham forward early on.</i>

482
00:49:00,767 --> 00:49:03,361
<i>He's picked out Munez.
Raul alongside him,</i>

483
00:49:03,447 --> 00:49:06,280
<i>but Munez goes
for goal and glory himself.</i>

484
00:49:06,367 --> 00:49:08,961
<i>Wanted the glory,
but I don't think Raul's happy.</i>

485
00:49:09,047 --> 00:49:11,003
<i>Perhaps he wanted that one squared.</i>

486
00:49:12,687 --> 00:49:14,166
<i>Raul!</i>

487
00:49:16,247 --> 00:49:19,080
<i>Ramos back to clear off the line.</i>

488
00:49:19,167 --> 00:49:21,203
<i>David Beckham now.</i>

489
00:49:21,287 --> 00:49:24,802
<i>Just about hooked away by Valencia.
Under a bit of pressure here.</i>

490
00:49:24,887 --> 00:49:30,678
<i>But now they can counter. Picked up by
Vicente, taken down by Santi Munez.</i>

491
00:49:30,767 --> 00:49:34,885
<i>Now Munez could be in real trouble here.
He is! It's a red card.</i>

492
00:49:34,967 --> 00:49:38,960
<i>Munez sent off
on his first start for Real Madrid.</i>

493
00:49:39,047 --> 00:49:41,163
<i>Well, it's unbelievable, isn't it?</i>

494
00:49:41,247 --> 00:49:43,715
<i>That's a man who's rusty.
A late challenge.</i>

495
00:49:43,807 --> 00:49:49,006
<i>He gave the referee nowhere to go.
Vicente was really clipped down.</i>

496
00:49:49,087 --> 00:49:50,998
<i>And it's a sad day for Munez.</i>

497
00:49:51,087 --> 00:49:53,920
<i>From dreams to nightmares
for Santi Munez.</i>

498
00:49:54,007 --> 00:49:57,124
<i>His first start,
and now his first early bath.</i>

499
00:49:59,167 --> 00:50:02,796
<i>Off comes Zinedine Zidane,
and it's Gavin Harris who will come on.</i>

500
00:50:08,767 --> 00:50:11,964
<i>Plenty of tackles flying in out there,
and that's Guti.</i>

501
00:50:12,047 --> 00:50:15,164
<i>Cañizares, what is he doing?
Not just with his hair either.</i>

502
00:50:15,247 --> 00:50:17,715
<i>This is not a typical
Real Madrid game, is it?</i>

503
00:50:17,807 --> 00:50:21,004
<i>The early sending-off
has really set the tone for the match.</i>

504
00:50:25,727 --> 00:50:28,799
<i>And another effort
blocked away by Casillas.</i>

505
00:50:28,887 --> 00:50:30,764
<i>And the follow-up just wide.</i>

506
00:50:30,847 --> 00:50:33,998
<i>Down to ten men,
it'll be very hard work for Real Madrid.</i>

507
00:50:34,087 --> 00:50:37,682
<i>They have to get their passing game
going. Beckham with a free kick.</i>

508
00:50:37,767 --> 00:50:40,645
<i>Even he's not quite
found his range tonight.</i>

509
00:50:46,967 --> 00:50:48,958
<i>David Beckham with the cross.</i>

510
00:50:49,047 --> 00:50:54,565
<i>Here's Gavin Harris! Goal for
Real Madrid! And they lead one-nil!</i>

511
00:50:54,647 --> 00:50:56,126
<i>The drought is over.</i>

512
00:50:56,207 --> 00:50:59,995
<i>That's a goal poacher's goal.
It was a great cross by Beckham.</i>

513
00:51:00,087 --> 00:51:03,363
<i>Harris is there in the six-yard area
doing what he does best,</i>

514
00:51:03,447 --> 00:51:05,517
<i>and stoops to conquer.</i>

515
00:51:06,127 --> 00:51:09,961
<i>So Real Madrid scraping home in the end,
that late goal from Gavin Harris.</i>

516
00:51:10,047 --> 00:51:12,845
<i>But Santiago Munez's
moment of madness</i>

517
00:51:12,927 --> 00:51:15,043
<i>nearly cost them the game,</i>

518
00:51:15,127 --> 00:51:17,436
<i>a red card he could
have no excuse about.</i>

519
00:51:17,527 --> 00:51:20,087
<i>It was a poor foul,
poor challenge, reckless.</i>

520
00:51:20,167 --> 00:51:23,079
<i>The referee had no option,
he had to go.</i>

521
00:51:23,167 --> 00:51:27,240
<i>Gavin, this was your first goal
in 17 games. How do you feel?</i>

522
00:51:28,567 --> 00:51:33,322
<i>It's a great day. I'm very happy.</i>

523
00:51:34,447 --> 00:51:37,678
<i>I'm going drinking with lots of girls.</i>

524
00:51:38,287 --> 00:51:39,276
<i>Good night.</i>

525
00:51:39,367 --> 00:51:41,403
Hello, hothead.

526
00:51:41,487 --> 00:51:42,886
Hello.

527
00:51:42,967 --> 00:51:45,481
Look, I have the solution
to all your problems.

528
00:51:46,327 --> 00:51:47,362
Really?

529
00:51:48,567 --> 00:51:50,080
Tequila, please.

530
00:51:51,047 --> 00:51:53,163
And I need you on my show tomorrow

531
00:51:53,247 --> 00:51:55,363
whilst you're still
playing for Madrid.

532
00:51:59,887 --> 00:52:01,366
You won't give up, will you?

533
00:52:02,927 --> 00:52:04,326
What do you think?

534
00:52:12,967 --> 00:52:14,002
Another?

535
00:52:14,087 --> 00:52:15,361
Another please.

536
00:52:16,927 --> 00:52:18,121
You started it. I didn't.

537
00:52:19,167 --> 00:52:20,156
Do you need a ride?

538
00:52:20,687 --> 00:52:21,756
No, thanks.

539
00:52:30,007 --> 00:52:32,567
- Bye.
- Bye.

540
00:52:44,407 --> 00:52:47,479
Sant? Darling?

541
00:52:48,927 --> 00:52:50,918
Sweetheart, wake up.

542
00:52:51,647 --> 00:52:55,481
Come on, sleepyhead. Darling?

543
00:52:55,567 --> 00:52:58,718
Look, I've brought you breakfast.
Do you want some juice?

544
00:52:58,807 --> 00:53:02,004
You've been asleep for ages. Here.

545
00:53:02,447 --> 00:53:05,166
- Sant.
- Why didn't you wake me up?

546
00:53:05,247 --> 00:53:07,966
- I tried. You were dead to the world.
- Try harder!

547
00:53:08,047 --> 00:53:10,515
- I told you to wake me up!
- I tried...

548
00:53:10,607 --> 00:53:13,599
You stupid?
I'm gonna miss the team plane!

549
00:53:13,687 --> 00:53:15,723
I'm not stupid. I'm not an alarm clock!

550
00:53:24,367 --> 00:53:28,565
- Hi. Trondheim, first class.
- OK. I'll see what I can do.



